<doc id="1162881" wikidata="Q1686215" url="?curid=1162881" title="Jeep SJ">
<text>Jeep&#x27;s SJ platform was part of the &quot;FSJ&quot; or full-size Jeep lineup. A &quot;FSJ&quot; is any vehicle produced in North America, carrying the &quot;Jeep&quot; nameplate, with 2 or 4 doors, in rear- or four-wheel drive, whose wheelbase does not exceed , nor is less than , and whose tread width is no more than nor less than . 

This definition is known to include the following models:

* 1963–1991 Jeep Wagoneer (renamed the “Grand Wagoneer” for the 1984 model year)
* 1963–1988 Jeep Gladiator (renamed the “J” series for 1972 model year)
* 1967–1969 Jeep M-715/724/725/726/6217 military versions
* 1974–1983 Jeep Cherokee

