<doc id="1163102" wikidata="Q9027425" url="?curid=1163102" title="Manidae">
<text>Manidae (&quot;spirits&quot;) is the only extant family of pangolins. This family comprises three genera (&quot;Manis&quot; from subfamily Maninae, &quot;Phataginus&quot; from subfamily Phatagininae, and &quot;Smutsia&quot; from subfamily Smutsiinae), as well as the extinct Fayum pangolin.

== Classification and phylogeny ==
=== History of classification ===
All species of living pangolin had been assigned to the genus &quot;Manis&quot; until the late 2000s, when research prompted the splitting of extant pangolins into three genera: &quot;Manis&quot;, &quot;Phataginus&quot;, and &quot;Smutsia&quot;.

=== Taxonomy ===
* Family: Manidae (pangolins)
** Subfamily: Maninae (Asian pangolins)
*** Genus: &quot;Manis&quot; (Asian pangolin)
**** (unranked): northern Asian clade
***** &quot;Manis pentadactyla&quot; (Chinese pangolin)
***** †&quot;Manis hungarica&quot; 
**** (unranked): southern Asian clade
***** &quot;Manis crassicaudata&quot; (Indian pangolin)
***** &quot;Manis&quot; sp. (&quot;Scale_H4&quot; &amp; &quot;Scale_H8&quot;)
***** †&quot;Manis lydekkeri&quot; 
***** Subgenus: &quot;Paramanis&quot; (Southeast Asian pangolin)
****** &quot;Manis javanica&quot; (Sunda pangolin)
****** &quot;Manis culionensis&quot; (Philippine pangolin)
****** †&quot;Manis palaeojavanica&quot; (giant Asian pangolin)
** (unranked): African clade
*** Subfamily: Phatagininae (small African pangolins)
**** Genus: &quot;Phataginus&quot; (African tree pangolin)
***** &quot;Phataginus tetradactyla&quot; (long-tailed pangolin)
***** &quot;Phataginus tricuspis&quot; (tree pangolin)
*** Subfamily: Smutsiinae (large African pangolins)
**** Genus: &quot;Smutsia&quot; (African ground pangolin)
***** &quot;Smutsia gigantea&quot; (giant pangolin)
***** &quot;Smutsia temmincki&quot; (ground pangolin)
***** †&quot;Smutsia olteniensis&quot; 
** &quot;Incertae sedis&quot;
*** †Manidae sp. [&quot;DPC 3972&quot; &amp; &quot;DPC 4364&quot;] (Fayum pangolin)


