<doc id="1163218" wikidata="Q517929" url="?curid=1163218" title="Cabeço Gordo">
<text>Cabeço Gordo (Portuguese for &quot;fat mound&quot;) is the highest point in the island of Faial, measuring above sea level. Located on the southern rim of the Caldeira Volcano, on a clear day, most of the islands of the central group of the Azores are visible: Pico, São Jorge, and Graciosa, although normally the caldera may be covered in clouds and fog.

