<doc id="1163271" wikidata="Q3361893" url="?curid=1163271" title="Cullen (plant)">
<text>Cullen is a genus of legumes (family Fabaceae) native to tropical, subtropical and arid regions of Africa, Asia and Australia. Despite the origin implied in the name of the constituent species &quot;Cullen americanum&quot;, legumes of this genus are not native to the Americas.

&quot;Cullen&quot; was previously included in broad definitions of the allied genus &quot;Psoralea&quot;.

